      <title>Sleeping man trapped by car crashing into his bedroom</title>
      <description><![CDATA[RIVERSIDE, CALIFORNIA <br/> A man was asleep in his bed when a car outside swerved off the road, knocked down a utility pole, drove through two front yards and came to a crashing stop through his bedroom wall at 1 a.m.<br/><br/>The incident on Saturday the 29th of February saw the man pinned between the vehicle and a wall of his house and had to be rescued by firefighters.<br/><br/>As he was trapped between a car and a hard place, he had to be removed with the 'jaws of life'.<br/><br/>Fortunately, the man avoided serious injuries and went to the hospital in minor condition.<br/><br/>Speaking to the Southern California News Group, Fire Department Battalion Chief Bruce Vanderhorst said, "He got very lucky." <br/><br/>The Police arrested a 22-year-old man, on suspicion of DUI, while the passenger was arrested on suspicion of public intoxication; both escaped injury, but not the law. <br/><br/>The fire department said that four people were living in the destroyed house, which was rendered uninhabitable. <br/><br/>According to their report, the total damage cost was a huge $200,000. <br/><br/>That'll wake anyone up.]]></description>
