      <title>Fast moo-ving cow on the loose, wanted by police</title>
      <description><![CDATA[PEMBROKE PINES, FLORIDA <br/> A deceptively fast moo-ving cow is on the loose in sunny Florida, which police have been trying weeks to catch.<br/>According to the Associated Press, the Pembroke Pines Police Department on Wednesday said the heifer was seen near Interstate 75 in southern Broward County. <br/>Apparently it's been on the lam since late January. <br/>The police tweeted out a photo titled "Wanted Unknown Cow" with the caption, "Description: Female cow. Brown with a white head. Faster than it looks. Talented fence jumper. Enjoys pool." Sounds kind of like a Tinder profile.<br/>Police spokeswoman Amanda Conwell said cops and wranglers have not been able to catch the animal and have backed off when it gets too close to roads with a lot of traffic. <br/>Authorities also say the cow is guilty of "MOOving violations, uddering false checks, and fleeing and eluding police."]]></description>
